  "time_ut": 1661854620,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "5\u0b86\u0bae\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0ba4\u0bca\u0b9f\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd  \u0baa\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb4\u0b95\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0ba3\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb2\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "You can apply to universities from 5th",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The University Grants Commission Chairman Prof. Sampath Amaratunga said that the preparations for admitting students to the universities are now ready and students can apply online from next Monday.",
        "He said the above while participating in the press conference held at the Government Information Department today (30).",
        "He said that this year, 42,519 students who have achieved high standards of achievement published on the 28th have been admitted to the university, out of which 2,035 students will be admitted to the Faculty of Medicine and 2,238 students will be admitted to the Faculty of Engineering.",
        "He said that the book published by the University Grants Commission will be sent to selected bookstores in all 3 languages \u200b\u200bon Friday this week and the book can be obtained from the said bookstores on Saturday.",
        "He also said that information related to bookstores will be published in the main newspapers published on Sundays.",
        "He informed that the process of requesting applications will be started on the 5th of September and students have been given a period of 03 weeks to submit the applications and the last date for sending the applications is the 23rd.",
        "He said that in case of any problem while selecting the universities, they can contact the telephone number 1919 of the government information center and get solutions on the telephone numbers of the university information center 0112695301 and 0112695302 from 8.00 am to 6.00 pm.",
        "He also said that you can visit the website www.ugc.ac.lk and watch the short videos in which the instructions are given in 03 languages \u200b\u200bSinhala, Tamil and English and it is necessary to watch the said video before filling the applications."
      ],
